uild of America Award|Producers Guild of America]] David L. Wolper Award \u2013 Outstanding Producer of Long-Form Television\n| ''The Night Manager''\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite news|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/producers-guild-unveils-tv-digital-nominees-961015|title=Producers Guild TV Nominees Include 'Westworld,' 'Stranger Things,' 'Atlanta'|newspaper=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2017\n| [[Empire Hero Award]]\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://empireonline.com/movies/features/three-empire-awards-2017-live-blog/ |title=Three Empire Awards 2017 Live Blog |last=Nugent |first=John |website=Empire |language=en |access-date=2017-03-19 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320062114/http://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/three-empire-awards-2017-live-blog/ |archivedate=20 March 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2017\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Actor \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy]]\n| ''[[Kong: Skull Island]]''\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/TeenChoiceFOX/status/876959044145078272|title=Your picks for #ChoiceSciFiMovieActor are @asabfb @prattprattpratt @dacremontgomery @diegoluna_ @Renner4Real @twhiddleston! #TeenChoicepic.twitter.com/aLHNZ6ah07|last=Awards|first=Teen Choice|date=2017-06-19|website=@TeenChoiceFOX|access-date=2017-06-20}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2018\n|[[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Scene Stealer]]\n|''[[Thor: Ragnarok]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/teen-choice-awards-black-panther-solo-riverdale-nominations-list-1202415855/|title=Teen Choice Awards: \u2018Black Panther\u2019, \u2018Solo\u2019, \u2018Riverdale\u2019 Lead Nominations \u2013 List|last=Evans|first=Greg|date=2018-06-22|work=Deadline|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2018\n|Indiana Film Journalists Association - Best Vocal/ Motion Capture Performance\n|''[[Early Man (film)|Early Man]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nextbestpicture.com/2/post/2018/12/the-2018-indiana-film-journalists-association-ifja-nominations.html|title=The 2018 Indiana Film Journalists Association (IFJA) Nominations|website=Next Best Picture|language=en|access-date=2019-07-13}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2019\n|[[BroadwayWorld]] UK Awards - Best Actor in a New Production of a Play\n|''[[Betrayal (play)|Betrayal]]''\n| {{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/westend/article/Shortlist-Announced-For-The-2019-BroadwayWorld-UK-Awards-Voting-Now-Open-20191021|title=Shortlist Announced For The 2019 BroadwayWorld UK Awards; Voting Now Open!|website=BroadwayWorld.com|language=en|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2019\n|[[Evening Standard Theatre Awards|Evening Standard Theatre Award for Best Actor]]\n|''Betrayal''\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/go/london/theatre/evening-standard-theatre-awards-2019-shortlist-in-full-a4277791.html|title=The 2019 Evening Standard Theatre Awards shortlist in full|date=2019-11-04|website=Evening Standard|language=en|access-date=2019-11-04}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2020\n|[[WhatsOnStage Award for Best Actor in a Play|WhatsonStage.com Award for Best Actor in a Play]]\n|''Betrayal''\n| {{pending}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whatsonstage.com/london-theatre/news/20th-annual-whatsonstage-awards-nominees_50480.html|title=20th Annual WhatsOnStage Awards nominees announced, including Andrew Scott, Claire Foy, & Juliet and more {{!}} WhatsOnStage|website=www.whatsonstage.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n<!--do NOT add rowspans-->\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n* <ref name=\"IC2007\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/culture/arts/theatre/article87703.ece |title=Rory Kinnear: the son also rises |last=Connors |first=Adrienne |date=27 April 2008 |work=[[The Sunday Times]] |accessdate=8 November 2014 |url-status=live |arch