ds with 3 awards each. |date=26 July 2012 |work=saturnawards.org |accessdate=27 July 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120626144753/http://www.saturnawards.org/ |archivedate=26 June 2012}}</ref>\n* <ref name=\"Glamour 2012\">{{cite web |last=David |first=Jessica |title=Woman of the Year Winners List 2012 |url= http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/celebrity/glamour-awards/winners-2012 |work=[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]] |date=29 May 2012 |accessdate=30 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120601221009/http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/celebrity/glamour-awards/winners-2012 |archivedate=1 June 2012}}</ref>\n* <ref name=MTV2013>{{cite web|title=2013 Movie Awards Winners |url=http://www.mtv.com/movies/person/166913/personmain.jhtml |publisher=MTV |accessdate=26 March 2014 |year=2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140326163555/http://www.mtv.com/movies/person/166913/personmain.jhtml |archivedate=26 March 2014}}</ref>\n* <ref name=Teen2012>{{cite web|title=Teen Choice Awards 2012: see full list of winners |url=http://www.ontheredcarpet.com/Teen-Choice-Awards-2012:-see-full-list-of-winners/8745074 |publisher=On The Red Carpet |accessdate=26 March 2014 |date=22 July 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140326155306/http://www.ontheredcarpet.com/Teen-Choice-Awards-2012%3A-see-full-list-of-winners/8745074 |archivedate=26 March 2014}}</ref>\n* <ref name=Kids2013>{{cite web|title=KCA 2013 Nominees |url=http://www.nick.com/kids-choice-awards/2013/nominees/ |publisher=Nick.com |accessdate=26 March 2014 |year=2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130325072602/http://www.nick.com/kids-choice-awards/2013/nominees/ |archivedate=25 March 2013 |df=dmy}}</ref>\n* <ref name=Standard2012>{{cite web|title=The London Evening Standard British Film Awards for 2012 Shortlist Revealed |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/goingout/film/the-london-evening-standard-british-film-awards-for-2012-shortlist-revealed-8452014.html |work=London Evening Standard |accessdate=26 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140326151055/http://www.standard.co.uk/goingout/film/the-london-evening-standard-british-film-awards-for-2012-shortlist-revealed-8452014.html |archivedate=26 March 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n* {{IMDb name|1089991}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n* {{Facebook|twhiddleston|Tom Hiddleston}}\n* {{Instagram|twhiddleston}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Tom Hiddleston\n|list  =\n{{Empire Award for Best Male Newcomer}}\n{{Evening Standard Theatre Award for Best Actor}} \n{{Glamour Awards Man of the Year}}\n{{GoldenGlobeBestActorTVMiniseriesFilm}}\n{{Laurence Olivier Award for Best Newcomer in a Play}}\n{{MTV Movie Award for Best Fight}}\n{{MTV Movie Award for Best Villain}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hiddleston, Tom}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People educated at The Dragon School]]\n[[Category:People educated at Eton College]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Pembroke College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]]\n[[Category:Best Male Newcomer Empire Award winners]]\n[[Category:English male film actors]]\n[[Category:English male radio actors]]\n[[Category:English male stage actors]]\n[[Category:English male television actors]]\n[[Category:English male video game actors]]\n[[Category:English male voice actors]]\n[[Category:English people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:Laurence Olivier Award winners]]\n[[Category:English male Shakespearean actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:English feminists]]\n[[Category:Male feminists]]\n[[Category:Best Miniseries or Television Movie Actor Golden Globe winners]]\n[[Category:People educated at Windlesham House School]]\n[[Category:People from Westminster]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the footballer|Tom Huddlestone}}\n{{short description|English actor, producer and musical performer}}\n{{good article}}\n{{pp-semi-blp|small=yes}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Tom Hiddleston\n| image              = Tom Hiddleston (36109110291) (cropped).jpg\n| caption            = Hiddleston at the 2017 [[San Diego Comic Con]]\n| birth_name         = Thomas William Hiddleston\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1981|2|9}}\n| birth_place        = [[Westminster]], [[London]], England\n| years_active       = 2001\u2013present\n| education          = {{ubl|[[Windlesham House School]]|[[Dragon School]]|[[Eton College]]}}\n| alma_mater         = {{ubl|[[University of Cambridge]]|[[Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]]}}\n| occupation         = Actor\n| signature          = File:Tom Hiddleston Sign.png\n}}\n\n'''Thomas William Hiddleston''' (born 9 February 1981) is an English actor. He is the recipient of [[Tom Hiddleston#Awards and nominations|several accolades]], including a [[Golden Globe Awards|Golden Globe Award]] and a [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Newcomer in a Play|Laurence Olivier Award]], and has been nominated for two [[Primetime Emmy Award]]s.\n\nHiddleston earned a [[double first]] in [[Classics]] at the [[University of Cambridge]] and later proceeded to study acting at the [[Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]]. At the beginning of his career, he appeared in [[West End theatre|West End]] productions of ''[[Cymbeline]]'' (2007) and ''[[Ivanov (play)|Ivanov]]'' (2008). He won the [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Newcomer in a Play|Olivier Award for Best Newcomer in a Play]] for his role in ''Cymbeline'' and was also nominated for the same award for his role as [[Michael Cassio|Cassio]] in ''[[Othello]]'' (2008). Hiddleston starred as the title character in a production of ''[[Coriolanus (2013 play)|Coriolanus]]'' (2013-2014) winning the [[Evening Standard Award|Evening Standard Theatre Award for Best Actor]] and receiving a nomination for the [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Actor|Olivier Award for Best Actor]]. He made his [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] debut in a 2019 revival of [[Betrayal (play)|''Betrayal'']].\n\nHiddleston made his film debut in the drama ''[[Unrelated]]'' (2007). He came to wider public attention when cast as [[Loki (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Loki]] in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]], appearing in ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]'' (2011), ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' (2012), ''[[Thor: The Dark World]]'' (2013), ''[[Thor: Ragnarok]]'' (2017), ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' (2018),''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'' (2019) and ''[[Loki (TV series)|Loki]]'' (2021).\n\nIn 2011, he won the [[17th Empire Awards|Empire Award for Best Male Newcomer]] and was nominated for the [[BAFTA Rising Star Award]]. He has also appeared in [[Steven Spielberg]]'s ''[[War Horse (film)|War Horse]]'' (2011), ''[[The Deep Blue Sea (2011 film)|The Deep Blue Sea]]'' (2011), [[Woody Allen]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Midnight in Paris]]'' (2011), the 2012 [[BBC]] series ''[[Henry IV, Part I and Part II (film series)|Henry IV]]'' and ''[[Henry V (2012 film)|Henry V]]'', and the romantic vampire film ''[[Only Lovers Left Alive]]'' (2013). In 2015, he starred in [[Guillermo del Toro]]'s ''[[Crimson Peak]]'', [[Ben Wheatley]]'s ''[[High-Rise (film)|High Rise,]]'' and played the troubled country music singer [[Hank Williams]] in the biopic ''[[I Saw the Light (film)|I Saw The Light]]''. The film ''[[Kong: Skull Island]]'' (2017) marked his first big-budget leading role outside [[Marvel Cinematic Universe|MCU]].\n\nHe starred in and was an executive producer of the [[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]] / [[BBC]] limited series ''[[The Night Manager (miniseries)|The Night Manager]]'' (2016), for which he received two [[Primetime Emmy Award]] nominations for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Limited Series or Movie|Outstanding Lead Actor in a Limited Series or Movie]] and [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Limited Series|Outstanding Limited Series]], and won his first [[Golden Globe Award]] for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film|Best Actor \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film]].\n\n==Early life==\nThomas William Hiddleston was born on 9 February 1981 in [[Westminster]], London,<ref name=tvg>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Guide|TVGuide.com]]| title=Tom Hiddleston|accessdate= 30 April 2012|url=https://tvguide.com/celebrities/tom-hiddleston/bio/325607| archivedate= 13 June 2016| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160613164230/http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/tom-hiddleston/bio/325607/ | url-status=live}}</ref> the son of Diana Patricia (''n\u00e9e'' Servaes) Hiddleston, an arts administrator and former stage manager, and Dr. James Norman Hiddleston, a physical chemist and former managing director of a biotech company that liaised with [[Oxford University]].<ref name=tie>{{cite book|last=Mosley|first=Charles|author2=Peter Hinton |author3=Hugh Peskett |author4=Roger Powell |title=Burke's Peerage, Baronetage & Knightage \u2013 107th Edition|publisher=Burke's Peerage; 107th edition|date=December 2003|page=4006|url=|isbn=9780971196629}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2011/nov/25/tom-hiddleston-deep-blue-sea|title=Tom Hiddleston: 'I never wanted to be the go-to guy for tails and waistcoats'|last=Brooks|first=Xan|date=2011-11-25|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-07-11|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> His father is from [[Greenock]], Scotland<ref name=\"Mirror2016\">{{cite news|title=Thor star Tom Hiddleston tells how ambition took him to the top- not plummy tones from Eton |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/thor-star-tom-hiddleston-tells-7564095 |work=[[Daily Mirror]] |date=15 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160420024413/http://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/thor-star-tom-hiddleston-tells-7564095 |archivedate=20 April 2016}}</ref> and his mother is from [[Suffolk]].<ref name=lto>{{cite web|first=James |last=Mottram |url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/arts-ents/film-tv-features/half-scottish-half-famous-all-talent-1.1089615 |title=Half Scottish, Half Famous ... All Talent |work=[[Herald Scotland]] |date=10 March 2011 |accessdate=17 April 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120518012859/http://www.heraldscotland.com/arts-ents/film-tv-features/half-scottish-half-famous-all-talent-1.1089615 |archivedate=18 May 2012 |df=dmy}}</ref> His younger sister, Emma, is also an actress, whilst his older sister, Sarah, is a journalist in India.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tom Hiddleston \u2013 \"The Avengers\" Movie Interview |url=http://www.whedon.info/Tom-Hiddleston-The-Avengers-Movie,40552.html |publisher=Whedon.com |date=3 January 2012 |accessdate=7 May 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120306125426/http://www.whedon.info/Tom-Hiddleston-The-Avengers-Movie%2C40552.html |archivedate=6 March 2012}}</ref> Through his mother, he is a great-grandson of Vice Admiral [[Reginald Servaes]] and a great-great-grandson of food producer [[Sir Edmund Vestey, 1st Baronet|Sir Edmund Vestey]].<ref>{{cite web|author1=Rebecca Cope |title=Our Guide to the Brit Pack |url=http://www.harpersbazaar.co.uk/culture-news/going-out/our-guide-to-the-brit-pack-tom-hiddleston-benedict-cumberbatch |work=[[Harper's Bazaar]] |accessdate=13 August 2014 |date=11 June 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715020633/http://www.harpersbazaar.co.uk/culture-news/going-out/our-guide-to-the-brit-pack-tom-hiddleston-benedict-cumberbatch |archivedate=15 July 2014}}</ref> His paternal grandfather, Alexander, served in the [[Royal Artillery]] and worked as a plater in the shipyards. He shares the same name as his great-great uncle, Tom Hiddleston, a shipyard plater from Greenock and a member of Royal Artillery's [[51st (Highland) Division]], who died after the [[Battle of the Somme]] and whose name is engraved in the Broomhill war memorial.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.greenocktelegraph.co.uk/news/14543206.actor-tom-hiddlestons-hidden-links-to-greenock/|title=Actor Tom Hiddleston's hidden links to Greenock|website=Greenock Telegraph|language=en|access-date=2019-07-11}}</ref>\n\nHiddleston was raised in [[Wimbledon, London|Wimbledon]] in his early years, and later moved to a village near [[Oxford]].<ref name=lto /> He started boarding at [[Windlesham House School]] at the age of seven, moving to the [[Dragon School]] in Oxford a year later.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Elizabeth Day |title=Tom Hiddleston: 'I'm fascinated by the private vulnerability of people' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/jan/24/tom-hiddleston-i-am-fascinated-by-private-vulnerability-the-night-manager |work=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=21 May 2018 |date=24 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dragonschool.org/old-dragons/news/our-history/eminent-dragons.html|title=Eminent Dragons|publisher=[[Dragon School]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120415131416/http://www.dragonschool.org/old-dragons/news/our-history/eminent-dragons.html|archivedate=15 April 2012|url-status=dead|accessdate=6 May 2012}}</ref> His parents divorced when he was 12.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2008/dec/21/tom-hiddleston-actor \"The actor who took centre stage: Tom Hiddleston\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818182135/https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2008/dec/21/tom-hiddleston-actor |date=18 August 2016}}. The Guardian. Retrieved 13 March 2017</ref> When discussing his parents' divorce in an interview with ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', he stated: \"I like to think it made me more compassionate in my understanding of human frailty.\"<ref>{{cite web|author1=Chloe Fox |title=Tom Hiddleston, interview: from Thor to a sell-out Coriolanus |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/theatre/10561842/Tom-Hiddleston-interview-from-Thor-to-a-sell-out-Coriolanus.html |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=4 March 2015 |date=14 January 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150214073914/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/theatre/10561842/Tom-Hiddleston-interview-from-Thor-to-a-sell-out-Coriolanus.html |archivedate=14 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nAt the age of 13, Hiddleston started at [[Eton College]], again as a boarder. He continued on to [[Pembroke College, Cambridge|Pembroke College]] at the [[University of Cambridge]], where he earned a [[double first]] in [[Classics]].<ref name=\"Mirror2016\"/><ref>{{cite web |last=Stewart |first=Thomas |title=Style Icon: Tom Hiddleston |url=http://www.mensfashionmagazine.com/style-icon-tom-hiddleston |work=Mens Fashion Magazine |accessdate=12 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313001406/http://www.mensfashionmagazine.com/style-icon-tom-hiddleston |archivedate=13 March 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Godwin |first=Richard |title=Faking Bad: Meet Hollywood's Nicest Villain, Tom Hiddleston |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/esmagazine/faking-bad-meet-hollywoods-nicest-villain-tom-hiddleston-8886197.html |work=[[London Evening Standard]] |accessdate=12 March 2014 |date=18 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140402043145/http://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/esmagazine/faking-bad-meet-hollywoods-nicest-villain-tom-hiddleston-8886197.html |archivedate=2 April 2014}}</ref> During his second term at Cambridge, he was seen in a production of ''[[A Streetcar Named Desire (play)|A Streetcar Named Desire]]'' by talent agent Lorraine Hamilton of Hamilton Hodell.<ref name=Telegraph2 /> He proceeded to study acting at the [[Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]], from which he graduated in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|title=Royal Academy of Dramatic Art \u2013 Tom Hiddleston |url=http://www.rada.ac.uk/profiles?prof_act=7889 |publisher=RADA |accessdate=12 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140312224852/http://www.rada.ac.uk/profiles?prof_act=7889 |archivedate=12 March 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2001\u20132010: Early work===\nWhile still doing student plays, Hiddleston began appearing on television, landing parts in [[Stephen Whittaker]]'s adaptation of ''[[Nicholas Nickleby]]'' (2001) for ITV,<ref name=Telegraph2>{{cite web|last=Patalay |first=Ajesh |title=Tom Hiddleston: Not Just a Romeo |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/3559452/Tom-Hiddleston-Not-just-a-Romeo.html |work=The Daily Telegraph |accessdate=12 March 2014 |date=30 August 2008 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140317230426/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/3559452/Tom-Hiddleston-Not-just-a-Romeo.html |archivedate=17 March 2014}}</ref> the [[BBC]]/[[HBO]] co-production ''[[Conspiracy (2001 film)|Conspiracy]]'' (2001), and as [[Randolph Churchill]], the son of [[Winston Churchill]], in the BBC/HBO drama ''[[The Gathering Storm (2002 film)|The Gathering Storm]]'' (2002).<ref>{{cite web|last=Sulcas |first=Roslyn |title=Thor's Nemesis Makes Some Thunder \u2013 Tom Hiddleston Gets Mythic for Thor: The Dark World |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/10/movies/tom-hiddleston-gets-mythic-for-thor-the-dark-world.html?_r=0 |work=New York Times |date=6 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150225122829/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/10/movies/tom-hiddleston-gets-mythic-for-thor-the-dark-world.html?_r=0 |archivedate=25 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nUpon graduating from RADA, Hiddleston was cast in his first film role, playing Oakley in [[Joanna Hogg]]'s first feature film, ''[[Unrelated]]'' (2006). His sister Emma also appeared in the film as Badge. Casting director, Lucy Bevan, who cast him in the film said \"there was just a fantastic confidence about him\". Hiddleston had leading roles in [[Declan Donnellan]]'s company [[Cheek by Jowl]]'s productions ''The Changeling'' (2006), and ''[[Cymbeline]]'' (2007). For the latter he won the [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Newcomer in a Play]].<ref name=OA1 /> His [[Donmar Warehouse]] credits include Cassio in [[Michael Grandage]]'s production of [[Shakespeare]]'s ''Othello'' (2008) alongside [[Chiwetel Ejiofor]] and [[Ewan McGregor]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/stage/theatre/article3001111.ece |work=[[The Times]] |location=London |title=Othello |first=Benedict |last=Nightingale |date=5 December 2007 |accessdate=25 May 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110615112824/http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/stage/theatre/article3001111.ece |archivedate=15 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://arts.guardian.co.uk/theatre/drama/reviews/story/0,,2224476,00.html |work=The Guardian |location=London |title=An Othello for Our Times |first=Susannah |last=Clapp |date=9 December 2007 |accessdate=25 May 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080118163833/http://arts.guardian.co.uk/theatre/drama/reviews/story/0%2C%2C2224476%2C00.html |archivedate=18 January 2008}}</ref> and Lvov in the West End revival of [[Chekhov]]'s ''[[Ivanov (play)|Ivanov]]'' (2008) with [[Kenneth Branagh]].<ref name=Telegraph2 />\n\nHiddleston was the voiceover for [[BBC]]'s documentary on the ''Galapagos Island'' in 2006.<ref name=HH>{{cite web|title=Tom Hiddleston \u2013 Hamilton Hodell \u2013 CV |publisher=Hamilton Hodell Talent Management |accessdate=16 April 2013 |url=http://www.hamiltonhodell.co.uk/cv/client_tom-hiddleston_id_100079.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130730181208/http://www.hamiltonhodell.co.uk/cv/client_tom-hiddleston_id_100079.htm |archivedate=30 July 2013}}</ref> He also narrated the [[audiobook]] ''[[The Red Necklace]]'' by [[Sally Gardner]] in 2007,<ref>Gardner, Sally. ''The Red Necklace''. [[Amazon.com]]. Retrieved 17 April 2012.</ref> Hiddleston played the leading role of Edward in Hogg's second feature, ''[[Archipelago (film)|Archipelago]]'' (2010).<ref>{{cite web|title=In Conversation: Lucy Bevan (Casting Director \u2013 Cinderella, Maleficent, An Education) |url=http://filmdoctor.co.uk/2015/03/18/in-conversation-lucy-bevan-casting-director-cinderella-maleficent-an-education/ |publisher=Film Doctor |accessdate=27 March 2015 |date=18 March 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150328214115/http://filmdoctor.co.uk/2015/03/18/in-conversation-lucy-bevan-casting-director-cinderella-maleficent-an-education/ |archivedate=28 March 2015}}</ref> His TV credits include Magnus Martinsson in the BBC detective drama ''[[Wallander (UK TV series)|Wallander]]'' (2008), Bill Hazledine in ''[[Suburban Shootout]]'' (2006), John Plumptre in the BBC costume drama TV film ''[[Miss Austen Regrets]]'' (2008) and William Buxton in the BBC drama series ''[[Return to Cranford]]'' (2009). In 2007, he joined a list of British actors, including [[Kate Winslet]] and [[Orlando Bloom]], to have guest starred in the long-running medical drama ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]''.<ref name=UKGQ>{{cite web |last=Naughton |first=John |title=Major Tom |url=http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/entertainment/articles/2013-11/01/tom-hiddleston-interview-and-pictures-thor-dark-world/page/3 |work=[[GQ]] |date=1 November 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140312212422/http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/entertainment/articles/2013-11/01/tom-hiddleston-interview-and-pictures-thor-dark-world/page/3 |archivedate=12 March 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===2011\u20132014: Career breakthrough===\n[[File:Tom Hiddleston (Avengers Red Carpet).jpg|thumb|At the New York premiere of ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' during the [[Tribeca Film Festival]] in April 2012]]\n\nHiddleston is well known for his portrayal of [[Loki (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Loki]] in the 2011 [[Marvel Studios]] film ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]''. He was invited to audition by [[Kenneth Branagh]], the film's director, after having previously worked with Branagh on ''Ivanov'' and ''Wallander''. Hiddleston said of Branagh, \"Ken has had a life-changing effect. He was able to say to the executives, 'Trust me on this, you can cast Tom and he will deliver'. It was massive and it's completely changed the course of what is available to me to do. Ken gave me my break.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Singh |first=Anita |title=Tom Hiddleston: Eton Unfairly Portrayed as 'Full of Braying Toffs' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/educationnews/9193004/Tom-Hiddleston-Eton-unfairly-portrayed-as-full-of-braying-toffs.html |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |location=UK |date=8 April 2012 |accessdate=12 April 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120411112256/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/educationnews/9193004/Tom-Hiddleston-Eton-unfairly-portrayed-as-full-of-braying-toffs.html |archivedate=11 April 2012}}</ref> In the beginning, he originally auditioned for the part of [[Thor (Marvel Comics)|Thor]]. \"I initially auditioned to play Thor. That was what I was being considered for, because I'm tall and blonde and classically trained, and that seemed to be the mold for what Thor was, he was to be a classical character. And it was in my auditions. I owe this entirely to Marvel and their open-mindedness, they saw something that they thought was interesting. They saw some temperament that they liked.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Leader |first=Michael |title=Tom Hiddleston Interview: The Avengers, Modern Myths, Playing Loki and More |url=https://denofgeek.com/movies/1337123/tom_hiddleston_interview_the_avengers_modern_myths_playing_loki_and_more.html |publisher=Den of Geek! |date=25 April 2012 |accessdate=7 May 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120430042246/http://www.denofgeek.com/movies/1337123/tom_hiddleston_interview_the_avengers_modern_myths_playing_loki_and_more.html |archivedate=30 April 2012}}</ref> The casting director gave Hiddleston six weeks to bulk up, so he went on a strict diet and gained twenty pounds of muscle.<ref name=ColliderThor>{{cite web|last=Weintraub |first=Steve |title=Tom Hiddleston on Set Interview ''Thor''; Talks About Playing Loki, How He Got Cast, and a Lot More |url=https://collider.com/tom-hiddleston-interview-thor-on-set/64233/ |publisher=Collider |date=10 December 2010 |accessdate=25 June 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120814045951/http://collider.com/tom-hiddleston-interview-thor-on-set/64233/ |archivedate=14 August 2012}}</ref> In the end, Branagh decided he was more suitable as the [[antagonist]] and cast him as Loki. The film magazine ''[[Empire (film magazine)|Empire]]'' ranked Hiddleston's portrayal as Loki the 19th Greatest Movie Character of All Time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://empireonline.com/100-greatest-movie-characters/default.asp?c=61 |title=The 100 Greatest Movie Characters/ 19. / Empire /|accessdate=2013-08-22 |work=Empire |publisher=Bauer Consumer Media }}</ref>\n\nIn November 2010, Hiddleston appeared with [[Benedict Cumberbatch]], [[Gemma Arterton]], [[Eddie Redmayne]] and [[Rose Byrne]] among others in [[Danny Boyle]]'s one time production of ''[[The Children's Monologues]]'', in which he played Prudence, a young girl upset with her mother for her father leaving and excited for her birthday. The play was a one time event of adapted stories of children's first-hand experiences in South Africa being re-interpreted by and performed by various actors.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Children's Monologues |url=http://www.thecrossedcow.com/2010/11/16/the-childrens-monologues/ |publisher=The Crossed Cow |accessdate=17 February 2014 |date=16 November 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131227213735/http://www.thecrossedcow.com/2010/11/16/the-childrens-monologues/ |archivedate=27 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Hiddleston portrayed novelist [[F. Scott Fitzgerald]] in writer-director [[Woody Allen]]'s ''[[Midnight in Paris]]''. He then played the noble Captain Nicholls in ''[[War Horse (film)|War Horse]]'', a film based on the 1982 novel by [[Michael Morpurgo]], directed by none other than [[Steven Spielberg]]. The same year he starred as Freddie Page, a [[Royal Air Force|RAF]] pilot in the drama ''[[The Deep Blue Sea (2011 film)|The Deep Blue Sea]]'', alongside [[Rachel Weisz]]. In 2012, he reprised his role as the supervillain Loki in ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]''. While filming a scene with [[Chris Hemsworth]], who plays [[Thor (Marvel Comics)|Thor]], the film's director, [[Joss Whedon]] told the fighting duo that the scene did not look real enough, so Hiddleston told Hemsworth to really hit him for the fight scene. \"I said to Chris, 'Dude, just hit me. Just hit me because I'm protected here and it's fine.' He's like, 'Are you sure?' I was like, 'Yeah, it will look great. Just go for it.'\"<ref>{{cite web|last=McDaniel |first=Matt |title='Avengers' star Tom Hiddleston told Chris Hemsworth to really hit him |url=https://movies.yahoo.com/blogs/movie-talk/avengers-tom-hiddleston-told-214048580.html |publisher=Yahoo! |date=2 May 2012 |accessdate=15 May 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/67h2sXdbt?url=http://movies.yahoo.com/blogs/movie-talk/avengers-tom-hiddleston-told-214048580.html |archivedate=16 May 2012 |url-status=live |df=dmy}}</ref> He provided the voiceover ''the Ancient Egyptian Book of the Dead'' in 2011 and poetry for ''iF Poems'' and ''The Love Book'' on [[iTunes]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iliterature.net/thelovebook/#the-actors |publisher=iLiterature |title=The Love Book App \u2013 The Actors |accessdate=16 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130923094407/http://www.iliterature.net/thelovebook/ |archivedate=23 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=iF Poems Educational app for kids: poetry for children ages 3\u201393! |url=http://ifpoems.com/#About+iF+Poems+App |publisher=if Poems |accessdate=12 April 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130608150159/http://ifpoems.com/ |archivedate=8 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn television in 2012, Hiddleston appeared in the [[BBC Two]] series ''[[The Hollow Crown (TV series)|The Hollow Crown]]'', portraying [[Henry V of England|Prince Hal]] opposite [[Jeremy Irons]] as [[Henry IV of England|Henry IV]] in the adaptation of Shakespeare's ''[[Henry IV, Part I and Part II (film series)|Henry IV, Part I]]'' and ''[[Henry IV, Part I and Part II (film series)|Part II]]''. He later appeared as King [[Henry V of England|Henry V]] in the television film ''[[Henry V (2012 film)|Henry V]]''.<ref>{{cite press release|title=Cast Confirmed for BBC Two's Cycle of Shakespeare Films |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/shakespeare-cast.html |publisher=BBC |date=24 November 2011 |accessdate=20 July 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/64JKhsWGc?url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/shakespeare-cast.html |archivedate=30 December 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy}}</ref> In 2013, Hiddleston played Loki again in ''[[Thor: The Dark World]]'',<ref>{{cite web|last=Eisenberg |first=Eric |title=Thor 2 To Shoot This Summer in London |url=https://cinemablend.com/new/Thor-2-Shoot-Summer-London-28724.html |publisher=Cinema Blend |date=9 January 2012 |accessdate=12 April 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120411150546/http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Thor-2-Shoot-Summer-London-28724.html |archivedate=11 April 2012}}</ref> following which he played a [[vampire]] in [[Jim Jarmusch]]'s film ''[[Only Lovers Left Alive]]'' with [[Tilda Swinton]] and [[Mia Wasikowska]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Roxborough |first=Scott |title=Tilda Swinton, John Hurt Join Jim Jarmusch's Vampire Film 'Only Lovers Left Alive' |url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/tilda-swinton-john-hurt-Jim-jarmusch-only-lovers-left-alive-285758 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=30 January 2012 |accessdate=12 April 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120501075738/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/tilda-swinton-john-hurt-Jim-jarmusch-only-lovers-left-alive-285758 |archivedate=1 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nFrom December 2013 to February 2014, Hiddleston played the title character in [[William Shakespeare]]'s ''[[Coriolanus (2013 play)|Coriolanus]]'' at the [[Donmar Warehouse]] in Covent Garden directed by [[Josie Rourke]]. It was also aired live internationally on 30 January 2014.<ref name=\"Mann\">{{cite web |url=http://www.london24.com/entertainment/theatre/tom_hiddleston_s_coriolanus_co_stars_revealed_1_2912804 |publisher=London 24 |title=Tom Hiddleston's Coriolanus Co-stars Revealed |date=22 October 2013 |first=Sebastian |last=Mann |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023062524/http://www.london24.com/entertainment/theatre/tom_hiddleston_s_coriolanus_co_stars_revealed_1_2912804 |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"Masters\">{{cite web|last=Masters |first=Tim |title=Tom Hiddleston Cast as Coriolanus at Donmar Warehouse |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-22596431 |publisher=BBC |date=20 May 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130905081921/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-22596431 |archivedate=5 September 2013}}</ref> David Benedict of ''Variety'' praised a \"scorching\" performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2013/legit/reviews/london-theater-review-coriolanus-starring-tom-hiddleston-1200969320/ |title=London Theater Review: 'Coriolanus' Starring Tom Hiddleston |first=David |last=Benedict |date=17 December 2013 |publisher= |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140124222849/http://variety.com/2013/legit/reviews/london-theater-review-coriolanus-starring-tom-hiddleston-1200969320/ |archivedate=24 January 2014}}</ref> He had a cameo in the 2014 film ''[[Muppets Most Wanted]]'', as the Great Escapo.<ref name=UKGQ />\n\n===2015\u2013present: Varied roles===\nHiddleston replaced [[Benedict Cumberbatch]] in the gothic horror film ''[[Crimson Peak]]'', directed by [[Guillermo del Toro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/guillermo-del-toros-crimson-peak-650845 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |title=Guillermo del Toro's 'Crimson Peak' Gets February 2014 Start Date |first=Etan |last=Vlessing |date=25 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027110527/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/guillermo-del-toros-crimson-peak-650845 |archivedate=27 October 2013}}</ref> The film started filming in Toronto in February 2014, and was released in October 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/guillermo-del-toros-crimson-peak-renamed-haunted-peak-will-spookily-materialize-in-theaters-april-2015-20131025 |publisher=Indie Wire |title=Updated: Guillermo Del Toro's 'Crimson Peak' Will Spookily Materialize In Theaters April 2015 |date=25 October 2013 |last=Taylor |first=Drew |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110222728/http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/guillermo-del-toros-crimson-peak-renamed-haunted-peak-will-spookily-materialize-in-theaters-april-2015-20131025 |archivedate=10 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2013/sep/09/tom-hiddleston-benedict-cumberbatch-crimson-peak |work=The Guardian |title=Tom Hiddleston poised to fill Benedict Cumberbatch's shoes on Crimson Peak |date=9 September 2013 |last=Child |first=Ben |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305010552/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2013/sep/09/tom-hiddleston-benedict-cumberbatch-crimson-peak |archivedate=5 March 2017}}</ref> He starred as Robert Laing in ''[[High-Rise (film)|High-Rise]]'' (2015), based on [[J. G. Ballard]]'s [[High Rise (novel)|novel of the same name]] and directed by [[Ben Wheatley]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Barraclough |first=Leo |title=Berlin: Tom Hiddleston to Star in Ben Wheatley's J.G. Ballard Adaptation 'High-Rise' |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/international/berlin-tom-hiddleston-to-star-in-ben-wheatleys-j-g-ballard-adaptation-high-rise-1201087581/ |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=5 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140205163931/http://variety.com/2014/film/international/berlin-tom-hiddleston-to-star-in-ben-wheatleys-j-g-ballard-adaptation-high-rise-1201087581/ |archivedate=5 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tom Hiddleston to film in Northern Ireland this June |url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2014-05-01/tom-hiddleston-to-film-in-northern-ireland-this-june |work=[[Radio Times]] |accessdate=7 May 2014 |date=1 May 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140506000632/http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2014-05-01/tom-hiddleston-to-film-in-northern-ireland-this-june |archivedate=6 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=Christine |title=Tom Hiddleston Spotted on the Set of 'High Rise' in Northern Ireland |url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2014/07/17/tom-hiddleston-spotted-on-the-set-of-high-rise-in-northern-ireland/ |publisher=On Location Vacations |accessdate=21 July 2014 |date=17 July 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140720230012/http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2014/07/17/tom-hiddleston-spotted-on-the-set-of-high-rise-in-northern-ireland/ |archivedate=20 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Tom Hiddleston (29341002162).jpg|thumb|Hiddleston at the Nerd HQ in July 2016.]]\n\nIn January 2014, Hiddleston became a spokesperson for [[Jaguar Cars]] in their \"Good to be Bad\" ad campaign featuring British actors in villain-themed commercials to promote Jaguars new models.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jaguar F-TYPE Commercial {{!}} It's Good To Be Bad \u2013 British Villains |url=http://www.jaguarusa.com/british-villains.html |publisher=Jaguar USA |accessdate=15 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150115192715/http://www.jaguarusa.com/british-villains.html |archivedate=15 January 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The first commercial of the campaign, titled \"Rendezvous\", first aired during the [[Super Bowl XLVII|2014 Super Bowl]] and featured Hiddleston along with [[Mark Strong]] and [[Ben Kingsley]].<ref>{{cite web|author1=Katey Rich |title=Tom Hiddleston, Ben Kingsley, and Mark Strong Get Evil For Super Bowl Jaguar Spot |url=http://www.vanityfair.com/vf-hollywood/tom-hiddleston-super-bowl |publisher=Vanity Fair |accessdate=15 January 2015 |date=28 January 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150115201452/http://www.vanityfair.com/vf-hollywood/tom-hiddleston-super-bowl |archivedate=15 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=Marc Graser |title=Nicholas Hoult Gets Evil for Jaguar |url=https://variety.com/2014/biz/news/nicholas-hoult-gets-evil-for-jaguar-1201322439/ |publisher=Variety |accessdate=15 January 2015 |date=6 October 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150207082217/http://variety.com/2014/biz/news/nicholas-hoult-gets-evil-for-jaguar-1201322439/ |archivedate=7 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2014, Hiddleston starred in another commercial in the campaign, titled \"The Art of Villainy\". It was released on YouTube, promoting the [[Jaguar F-Type|F-Type coupe]]. However, the [[Advertising Standards Authority (United Kingdom)|Advertising Standards Authority]] received complaints about the video \"encouraging irresponsible driving\". [[Jaguar Land Rover]] said that in the ad, when the car did leave the car park, it \"accelerated briefly\" and that police were present at filming to confirm the speed limit was not breached but the ASA ruled against it and banned the commercial.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Mark Sweney |title=Jaguar 'villain' ad banned for encouraging irresponsible driving |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2014/jul/16/jaguar-ad-tom-hiddleston-banned-youtube |publisher=The Guardian |accessdate=15 January 2015 |date=16 July 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150115192314/http://www.theguardian.com/media/2014/jul/16/jaguar-ad-tom-hiddleston-banned-youtube |archivedate=15 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nIt was announced in June 2014 that Hiddleston would play country music singer [[Hank Williams]] in the 2015 biopic ''[[I Saw the Light (film)|I Saw the Light]]'', based on the 1994 biography. The film was directed by [[Marc Abraham]], and was first shown in the Special Presentations section of the [[2015 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/sandra-bullocks-our-brand-tom-hiddlestons-i-saw-the-light-to-premiere-at-toronto-1201572271/ |title=Sandra Bullock's 'Our Brand Is Crisis,' Robert Redford's 'Truth' to Premiere at Toronto |accessdate=18 August 2015 |work=Variety}}</ref> The film was released on 25 March 2016, by [[Sony Pictures Classics]].<ref name=\"releasedate\">{{cite news|last=Hammond|first=Pete|url=https://deadline.com/2015/10/i-saw-the-light-moves-oscar-casualty-sony-pictures-classics-1201585220/|title=Oscar Casualty: Sony Pictures Classics Sees The Light, Moves Hank Williams Biopic To March|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=16 October 2015|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref> Although the film wasn't well received, Hiddleston's performance was widely praised by critics.<ref>{{Citation|title=I Saw the Light (2016)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/i_saw_the_light|language=en|access-date=2019-07-10}}</ref> [[Stephanie Zacharek]] of [[Time (magazine)|Time]] called him \"magnificent\" adding that \"he honors Williams\u2019 greatness but also wriggles beyond it.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/4263607/review-born-to-be-blue-i-saw-the-light-miles-ahead/|title=Review: 3 Not-Really-Biopics Reimagine the Lives of Chet Baker, Miles Davis and Hank Williams|website=Time|language=en|access-date=2019-07-10}}</ref>\n\nHiddleston was one of the narrators in the 2015 documentary ''[[Unity (film)|Unity]]'' directed by [[Shaun Monson]].<ref>{{cite web|author1=Dave McNary |title=Documentary 'Unity' Set for Aug. 12 Release with 100 Star Narrators |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/documentary-unity-set-for-aug-12-release-with-100-star-narrators-1201477200/ |publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=1 May 2015 |date=22 April 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160422092206/http://variety.com/2015/film/news/documentary-unity-set-for-aug-12-release-with-100-star-narrators-1201477200/ |archivedate=22 April 2016}}</ref> He appeared as Jonathan Pine in the 2016 television mini-series ''[[The Night Manager (miniseries)|The Night Manager]]'' based on the espionage and detective novel of the [[The Night Manager|same name]] by [[John le Carr\u00e9]]. The series started filming in Spring 2015 and aired on [[BBC]] and [[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]] with [[Hugh Laurie]] also starring.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hugh Laurie and Tom Hiddleston to Star in The Night Manager |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2015/night-manager-casting |publisher=BBC |accessdate=4 March 2015 |date=12 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150214013749/http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2015/night-manager-casting |archivedate=14 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=Lesley Goldberg |title=AMC Lands Hugh Laurie, Tom Hiddleston Limited Series 'Night Manager' |url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/amc-lands-hugh-laurie-tom-741403 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=4 March 2015 |date=30 October 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150309231828/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/amc-lands-hugh-laurie-tom-741403 |archivedate=9 March 2015}}</ref> Ben Travers of [[IndieWire]] noted that he carried the role of Pine from start to finish, \"with an admirable determination and aptly unbreakable constitution.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2016/04/review-the-night-manager-perfectly-tells-a-classic-or-is-it-cliche-story-289748/|title=Review: 'The Night Manager' Perfectly Tells a Classic \u2014 Or Is It Cliche? \u2014 Story|last=Travers|first=Ben|last2=Travers|first2=Ben|date=2016-04-19|website=IndieWire|language=en|access-date=2019-07-10}}</ref> For his performance in the series he was nominated for several awards, including two [[Primetime Emmy Award]]s and won a [[Golden Globe Award]] for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film|Best Actor]].\n\n[[File:Tom Hiddleston (48468955071).jpg|thumb|left|Hiddleston at the 2019 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]]]\n\nIn early 2017 he expressed his will to take a long break from work, and his desire to work again in theater.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/216210/tom-hiddleston-takes-break|title=Tom Hiddleston takes a break from it all|last=Nepales|first=Ruben V.|website=entertainment.inquirer.net|language=en|access-date=2019-06-18}}</ref> Later the same year, Hiddleston starred in [[Legendary Pictures]]' [[King Kong]] film, ''[[Kong: Skull Island]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2014/09/skull-island-tom-hiddleston-king-kong-835067/|title=Legendary's 'Skull Island'; Tom Hiddleston Stars, Jordan Vogt-Roberts Helms King Kong Origin Tale|last=Fleming, Jr|first=Mike|date=16 September 2014|website=Deadline Hollywood|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140916215935/http://deadline.com/2014/09/skull-island-tom-hiddleston-king-kong-835067/|archivedate=16 September 2014|url-status=live|accessdate=16 September 2014}}</ref> Released on 10 March, and directed by [[Jordan Vogt-Roberts]], ''Kong: Skull Island'' was a commercial success, earning over $566 million worldwide and received generally positive reviews.<ref>{{Citation|title=Kong: Skull Island|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/kong-skull-island|access-date=2019-08-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2014/12/kong-skull-island-2017-zhang-yimou-great-wall-1201322632/|title=King Kong Pic 'Skull Island' Moves To 2017; Zhang Yimou's 'Great Wall' Epic Dated For 2016|last=Yamato|first=Jen|date=12 December 2014|website=Deadline Hollywood|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213094101/http://deadline.com/2014/12/kong-skull-island-2017-zhang-yimou-great-wall-1201322632/|archivedate=13 December 2014|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=legendary2016.htm|title=Kong: Skull Island (2017) - Box Office Mojo|website=www.boxofficemojo.com|access-date=2019-07-10}}</ref> In September 2017 he played the title character in a limited run of [[William Shakespeare]]'s ''[[Hamlet]]'' directed by [[Kenneth Branagh]]. The production ran for three weeks at a 160-seat theater, with the tickets given out by lottery system to raise money for [[RADA]].<ref name=\":0\" /> [[Michael Billington (critic)|Michael Billington]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' called his performance \"a compelling Hamlet with a genuine nobility of soul.\" [[Ann Treneman]] of ''[[The Times]]'' praised his performance writing that he made the role \"completely his own, emotional, magnetic, canny, often frolicsome\" and that is \"a shame is that so few will see his HiddleHamlet.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.londontheatre.co.uk/theatre-news/west-end-features/tom-hiddlestons-hamlet-what-do-the-reviews-say|title=Tom Hiddleston's Hamlet: What do the reviews say?|last=Longman|first=Will|date=|website=London Theatre Guide|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=2019-07-10}}</ref>\n\nHe reprised his role as Loki in ''[[Thor: Ragnarok]]'', released on 3 November 2017,<ref name=\"Ruffalo2\">{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2015/10/15/mark-ruffalo-will-bring-hulk-thor-ragnarok|title=Mark Ruffalo will bring the Hulk to Thor: Ragnarok|last=Breznican|first=Anthony|date=15 October 2015|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6cNIxJrM5?url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/10/15/mark-ruffalo-will-bring-hulk-thor-ragnarok|archivedate=18 October 2015|url-status=live|accessdate=16 October 2015|quote=He also confirmed at the time that Tom Hiddleston would be returning as the villain Loki.|df=dmy}}</ref> and also appeared in ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' (2018) and ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'' (2019).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/news/a607266/loki-to-appear-in-thor-ragnarok-and-both-parts-of-avengers-infinity-war.html|title=Loki to appear in Thor: Ragnarok and both parts of Avengers: Infinity War|last=Babbage|first=Rachel|date=1 November 2014|work=Digital Spy|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6TlZmNL8m?url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/news/a607266/loki-to-appear-in-thor-ragnarok-and-both-parts-of-avengers-infinity-war.html?utm_source%3Dtwt%26utm_medium%3Dsnets%26utm_campaign%3Dtwitter|archivedate=1 November 2014|url-status=dead|accessdate=2 November 2014|df=}}</ref> All three films were well received with ''Endgame'' earning over $2 billion worldwide to rank as the [[List of highest-grossing films|highest-grossing film]] of all time.<ref>{{Citation|title=Thor: Ragnarok (2017)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/thor_ragnarok_2017|language=en|access-date=2019-07-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/world/|title=All Time Worldwide Box Office Grosses|website=www.boxofficemojo.com|access-date=2019-07-10}}</ref> He voiced the villain in [[Nick Park]]'s animated film ''[[Early Man (film)|Early Man]]'' which was released in early 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/eddie-redmayne-early-man-lionsgate-1202445069/|title=Eddie Redmayne's 'Early Man' to Be Released by Lionsgate in North America|last=McNary|first=Dave|date=2017-05-25|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-11}}</ref> In 2019, he starred as Robert from 5 March to 8 June in a revival of [[Harold Pinter]]'s [[Betrayal (play)|''Betrayal'']] at the [[Harold Pinter Theatre]], directed by [[Jamie Lloyd (director)|Jamie Lloyd]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whatsonstage.com/london-theatre/news/tom-hiddleston-betrayal-jamie-lloyd-play-confirmed_48017.html|title=Tom Hiddleston to star in Betrayal as part of West End Pinter season {{!}} WhatsOnStage|website=www.whatsonstage.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-01-25}}</ref> The play premiered to positive reviews and succeeded to have a sold-out [[West End theatre|West End]] run, with [[Henry Hitchings]] of ''[[Evening Standard]]'' finding him to be \"irresistibly magnetic\" with an impressive \"poise and sensitivity\" in his part.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/go/london/theatre/betrayal-reviews-roundup-pinter-tom-hiddleston-play-a4091416.html|title=What the critics had to say about Betrayal starring Tom Hiddleston|date=2019-03-14|website=Evening Standard|language=en|access-date=2019-08-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/go/london/theatre/betrayal-review-tom-hiddleston-london-theatre-pinter-a4091281.html|title=Betrayal review \u2014 Tom Hiddleston brings poise and pathos|date=2019-03-14|website=Evening Standard|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> In August 2019 he made his [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] debut reprising his role of Robert in ''Betrayal'', as the production transferred to Broadway for a 17-week limited engagement at the [[Bernard B. Jacobs Theatre]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/tom-hiddleston-will-make-broadway-debut-in-betrayal|title=Tom Hiddleston Will Make Broadway Debut in Betrayal|last=McPhee|first=Ryan|date=|website=Playbill|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=2019-06-30}}</ref> Reviewing the Broadway staging in [[Variety (magazine)|''Variety'']], [[Marilyn Stasio]] called his performance \u201ca striking physical, as well as an emotionally complicated one.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/legit/reviews/betrayal-review-tom-hiddleston-broadway-1203323155/|title=Broadway Review: \u2018Betrayal\u2019 With Tom Hiddleston|last=Stasio|first=Marilyn|date=2019-09-06|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>\n\n==== Upcoming projects ====\nOn 8 November 2018, it was announced that Hiddleston would be reprising his role as Loki in a new Marvel limited series centered on the character which will air on Disney's upcoming streaming service, [[Disney+]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/new-marvel-series-for-disney-to-star-tom-hiddleston-as-loki/|title=New Marvel series on Disney+ to star Tom Hiddleston as Loki|last=Petrakovitz|first=Caitlin|publisher=CNet|date=8 November 2018|accessdate=9 November 2018}}</ref> He is also set to voice the same character in the animated series ''[[What If...? (TV series)|What If...?]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/marvels-what-if-announces-massive-voice-cast-of-mcu-stars-jeffrey-wright-as-the-watcher/|title=Marvel's 'What If?' Announces Massive Voice Cast of MCU Stars & Jeffrey Wright as The Watcher|last=Mancuso|first=Vinnie|date=2019-07-21|website=Collider|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-19}}</ref> In February 2020, it was announced that he is set to star in [[Netflix]] political thriller series ''White Stork''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/tom-hiddleston-star-netflix-political-thriller-series-white-stork-1202851433/|title=Tom Hiddleston To Star In Netflix Political Thriller Series \u2018White Stork\u2019|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2020-02-04|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> Hiddleston is in talks to reprise his role in a second series of ''[[The Night Manager (TV series)|The Night Manager]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/ustv/a25957545/night-manager-series-2-tom-hiddleston-how-character-returns/|title=Hiddleston has as many Night Manager season 2 questions as you do|last=Harp|first=Justin|date=2019-01-19|website=Digital Spy|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref> He is attached to star in a [[Ben Wheatley]]'s adaptation of [[Frank Miller (comics)|Frank Miller]]'s comic book mini-series ''[[Hard Boiled (comics)|Hard Boiled]]'' produced by [[Warner Bros]] and in a [[James Ivory]]'s adaptation of [[Shakespeare]]'s ''[[Richard II (play)|Richard II]]'' as the eponymous character.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theplaylist.net/rotterdam-ben-wheatley-talks-free-fire-doctor-killer-approach-wages-fear-remake-20170206/2/|title=Rotterdam: Ben Wheatley Talks 'Free Fire,' 'Doctor Who' And His Killer Approach To The 'Wages Of Fear' Remake - Page 2 of 2|website=theplaylist.net|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/james-ivory-adapting-call-me-by-your-name-his-film-legacy-1075848|title=James Ivory on His Film Legacy and Adapting 'Call Me by Your Name'|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life and off-screen work ==\nHiddleston lives in the [[Belsize Park]] area of north-west London.<ref>{{cite web|title=Marvel Avengers Assemble - interview |url=http://www.indielondon.co.uk/Film-Review/marvel-avengers-assemble-tom-hiddleston-interview |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827174128/http://www.indielondon.co.uk/Film-Review/marvel-avengers-assemble-tom-hiddleston-interview |archivedate=27 August 2016}}<br />{{cite web|title=Tom Hiddleston Says It's 'Exotic To Be An Actor In London,' Talks New Movie 'High-Rise' |url=http://www.designntrend.com/articles/61774/20150929/tom-hiddleston-says-its-exotic-be-actor-london-talks-new-movie-high-rise.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117063413/http://www.designntrend.com/articles/61774/20150929/tom-hiddleston-says-its-exotic-be-actor-london-talks-new-movie-high-rise.htm |archivedate=17 November 2016}}</ref> He has donated items for auction and has supported several charities, including: Small Steps Project, [[Starlight Children's Foundation]], Cure [[Epidermolysis bullosa|EB]], [[Comic Relief]], [[Red Nose Day USA]], [[Thomas Coram Foundation for Children]], [[Great Ormond Street Hospital]], [[Amnesty International]] and [[Chance to Shine]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Benedict Cumberbatch, Tom Hiddleston, Jo Brand and more celebrities design and sign cards for UK's first children's charity |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/benedict-cumberbatch-tom-hiddleston-jo-3504331 |publisher=Mirror Online |accessdate=7 May 2014 |author=Rebecca Pocklington |date=6 May 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140507105641/http://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/benedict-cumberbatch-tom-hiddleston-jo-3504331 |archivedate=7 May 2014}}<br />{{Cite web|url=https://officiallondontheatre.com/news/tom-hiddleston-kit-harington-stars-pinter-birthday-gala/|title=Tom Hiddleston, Kit Harington & more stars in Pinter birthday gala|website=Official London Theatre|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-06-22}}<br />{{Cite web|url=http://www.smallstepsproject.org/portfolio/tom-hiddleston/|title=Tom Hiddleston|website=Small Steps Project|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-22}}<br />{{Cite web|url=https://www.omaze.com/products/tom-hiddleston-london-theater|title=Meet Tom Hiddleston for a Drink in London & Sit VIP at His Show|website=Omaze|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-22}}<br />{{Cite web|url=https://www.comicrelief.com/press-releases/win-breakfast-david-attenborough-comic-relief-prizeathon|title=Win breakfast with David Attenborough in Comic Relief Prizeathon|website=Comic Relief|language=en|access-date=2019-06-22}}<br />{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/goshcharity/status/398419290971316224?lang=el|title=Huge thanks to @twhiddleston for auctioning this great Loki self-portrait for @GreatOrmondSt|last=Charity|first=GOSH|date=|website=@goshcharity|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=2019-06-22}}<br />{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/CureEBorg/status/1126147328568647680|title=Are you a  #TomHiddleston fan? Meet @twhiddleston in his dressing room after a performance of 'Betrayal' at the Pinter Theatre in London - this and many wonderful prizes to auction at our #SilverButterflyDinner on the 16th May 2019. Help us|last=EB|first=Cure|date=2019-05-08|website=@CureEBorg|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=2019-06-22}}</ref>\n\nHe is a UK ambassador of the humanitarian and developmental assistance fund group [[UNICEF]]. He traveled to [[Guinea]] in early 2013 to raise awareness about hunger and malnutrition,<ref>{{cite web|author1=Frances Wasem |title=Tom Hiddleston Reports on Visiting Guinea for UNICEF |url=http://www.harpersbazaar.co.uk/culture-news/news/unicef-supporter-tom-hiddleston-on-the-plight-of-children-in-guinea |work=Harpers Bazaar |accessdate=3 June 2014 |date=7 March 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606223006/http://www.harpersbazaar.co.uk/culture-news/news/unicef-supporter-tom-hiddleston-on-the-plight-of-children-in-guinea |archivedate=6 June 2014}}</ref> and to South Sudan in early 2015 and late 2016 to report the results of the ongoing [[South Sudanese Civil War|civil war]] on the lives of vast numbers of children across the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unicef.org/press-releases/unicef-ambassador-tom-hiddleston-returns-south-sudan-brutal-conflict-enters-its|title=UNICEF Ambassador Tom Hiddleston returns to South Sudan as the brutal conflict enters its fourth year|website=www.unicef.org|language=en|access-date=2019-01-04}}</ref> Hiddleston is a self-described [[feminist]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elleuk.com/now-trending/david-cameron-afraid-feminist-shirt-meaning |work=Elle |title=Why is David Cameron so afraid to call himself a feminist? |author1=Natasha Pearlman |date=27 October 2014 |accessdate=1 May 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150320145448/http://www.elleuk.com/now-trending/david-cameron-afraid-feminist-shirt-meaning |archivedate=20 March 2015}}</ref> In February 2018 he was named as one of the donators by ''Justice and Equality Fund'', the UK version of [[Time's Up (movement)|Time's Up]] movement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rosauk.org/blog/over-1000000-awarded-from-the-justice-and-equality-fund-supported-by-times-up-uk-to-specialist-organisations-across-the-uk-to-help-women-who-have-experienced-sexual-harassment-and-abuse/|title=Rosa \u00bb Over \u00a31,000,000 awarded from The Justice and Equality Fund, supported by TIME'S UP UK, to specialist organisations across the UK to help women who have experienced sexual harassment and abuse|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-04}}</ref> He is also an ambassador of the ''Illuminating [[BAFTA]]'' campaign, an action which aims to provide opportunities to those who otherwise wouldn't have been given a chance in the film, games and television industries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bafta.org/about/fundraising/ambassadors-supporters|title=Ambassadors & Supporters|date=2018-10-24|website=www.bafta.org|language=en|access-date=2019-01-25}}</ref>\n<!--Do NOT add any relationships that haven't been officially confirmed by Hiddelston and/or his partners; this is not a place for gossip or speculation-->\n\nHiddleston was previously in a relationship with actress [[Susannah Fielding]], who appeared with him in an episode of ''[[Wallander (UK TV series)|Wallander]]'' in 2008. Their relationship ended in late 2011.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.scotsman.com/lifestyle/culture/film/interview-tom-hiddleston-actor-1-1976625|title=Interview: Tom Hiddleston, actor|access-date=2018-09-20|language=en}}<br />{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2011/nov/25/tom-hiddleston-deep-blue-sea|title=Tom Hiddleston: 'I never wanted to be the go-to guy for tails and waistcoats'|last=Brooks|first=Xan|date=2011-11-25|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-09-20}}<br />{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/soldier-of-fortune-tom-hiddleston-is-set-to-become-2012s-hottest-new-star-6284844.html|title=Soldier of fortune: Tom Hiddleston is set to become 2012's hottest new|work=The Independent|access-date=2018-09-20|language=en-GB}}</ref> In 2016, Hiddleston dated American singer-songwriter [[Taylor Swift]] for several months.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gq.com/story/tom-hiddleston-cover-profile|title=Tom Hiddleston on Taylor Swift, Heartbreak, and that Tank Top|last=Brodesser-Akner|first=Taffy|date=2017-02-14|work=GQ|access-date=2018-09-20|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Media image and acting style ==\n[[File:Kong- Skull Island Japan Premiere Red Carpet- Tom Hiddleston (37422472335).jpg|thumb|Hiddleston at the Japan premiere of ''[[Kong: Skull Island]]'' in 2017]]\n\nOne of the highest profile actors in contemporary [[British popular culture]], Hiddleston appeared on [[Debrett's]] 2017 list of the most influential people in the UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/0/debretts-500-list-stage-screen/|title=Debrett's 500 List: Stage & Screen|date=21 January 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211144411/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/0/debretts-500-list-stage-screen/|archivedate=11 February 2017|url-status=live|publisher=The Telegraph}}</ref> In 2015 he was named [[British Film Institute]]'s first official founding ambassador.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bfi.org.uk/news-opinion/news-bfi/announcements/tom-hiddleston-becomes-founding-bfi-ambassador|title=Tom Hiddleston becomes founding BFI Ambassador|website=British Film Institute|language=en|access-date=2018-12-21}}</ref> Hiddleston won the light-hearted UK award [[Rear of the Year]] 2016, in which the public nominate the male and female UK-based celebrities that they think should win the titular award.<ref>{{cite web|date=29 July 2016|title=Past winners of Rear of the Year|url=http://www.rearoftheyearcompetition.com/past-winners/}}</ref> He has been named most stylish/best dressed man in several lists.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/article/tom-hiddleston-tops-glamour-best-dressed-list|title=Tom Hiddleston tops GLAMOUR\u2019s Best Dressed Man list|last=Bayley|first=Leanne|website=Glamour UK|access-date=2019-03-16}}<br />{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/most-stylish-man-of-2017-winner|title=This Is Your Most Stylish Man of 2017|last=Nast|first=Cond\u00e9|website=GQ|language=en|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref> [[Taffy Brodesser-Akner]] of ''[[GQ]]'' described his off-screen persona as \"a sweet-natured bookworm given the face and body of the only man who should ever be allowed to wear a suit\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/tom-hiddleston-cover-profile|title=Tom Hiddleston GQ profile|last=Brodesser-Akner|first=Taffy|date=February 14, 2017|website=gq|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=March 16, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Crimson Peak]]'' director [[Guillermo del Toro]] and [[comic book]] writer [[Stan Lee]] have called him \"the nicest guy on earth/you'll ever meet\" with del Toro adding that he ruined the usual barrier of being either nice, or good-looking.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2014/07/crimson-peak-tom-hiddleston-comic-con.html|title=Guillermo del Toro Tells Shocked Comic-Con Crowd That Tom Hiddleston Is Great|last=|first=|date=|website=www.vulture.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=2019-03-16}}<br />{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/therealstanlee/status/65554434813468672?lang=el|title=And if you want a cooler than cool villain who's also the nicest guy you'll ever meet\u2014I give you Loki's alter ego, Tom Hiddleston.|last=lee|first=stan|date=May 3, 2011|website=@therealstanlee|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=March 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\nKenneth Branagh noted that the first time he ever saw Hiddleston, playing Cassio in ''[[Othello]]'', it was quite clear to him that he was an utterly naturalistic speaker of [[William Shakespeare|Shakespeare]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/a794870/tom-hiddleston-was-so-effortlessly-charming-kenneth-branagh-remembers-discovering-a-star/|title=Kenneth Branagh remembers discovering Tom Hiddleston|last=Jeffery|first=Morgan|date=2016-05-20|website=Digital Spy|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-03-15}}</ref> [[Michael Billington (critic)|Michael Billington]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' wrote that Hiddleston's key acting quality is \"his ability to combine a sweet sadness with an incandescent fury, suggesting a fierce intellect gnawed by intense melancholy and yet subjecting to bouts of intemperate rage.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2017/sep/02/hamlet-review-lucky-few-see-tom-hiddleston-combine-sweet-sadness-with-incandescent-fury|title=Hamlet review \u2013 lucky few see Tom Hiddleston combine sweet sadness with incandescent fury|last=Billington|first=Michael|date=2017-09-01|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-03-15|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> [[Charles McNulty]] of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' described Hiddleston as \"an actor of uncommon intelligence and [[Pre-Raphaelite Brotherhood|Pre-Raphaelite]] beauty.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/story/2019-11-19/broadway-american-utopia-slave-play-sound-inside|title=Commentary: Everyone wants a piece of Broadway, but what is Broadway these days?|date=2019-11-19|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-20}}</ref> Hiddleston spent nearly five weeks preparing for the role of [[Hank Williams]], performing seven of the movie's soundtrack songs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/138194-tom-hiddlestons-i-saw-the-light-soundtrack-will-feature-lots-of-country-goodness|title=Hiddleston Owns The 'I Saw The Light' Soundtrack|last=Bowman|first=Sabienna|website=Bustle|language=en|access-date=2019-03-15}}</ref> He has claimed that [[method acting]] is not easy for him because it does not help him as a collaborator.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/film-tv/a14835/tom-hiddleston-i-saw-the-light-interview/|title=Tom Hiddleston on Playing Hank Williams: \"I Had to Go to Some Pretty Dark Places\"|last=Kosin|first=Julie|date=2016-03-29|website=Harper's BAZAAR|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-15}}</ref> ''[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]''{{'}}s Dominic Cavendish suggested that Hiddleston \"has got the theatrical acting chops to head up there among the greats\", and ''[[The Independent]]''{{'}}s Paul Taylor said that \"his range is beginning to look pretty limitless\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/theatre/what-to-see/betrayal-review-harold-pinter-theatre-tom-hiddleston-displays/|title=Betrayal review, Harold Pinter Theatre: Tom Hiddleston displays a hypnotic sensitivity in this modern masterpiece|last=Cavendish|first=Dominic|date=2019-03-14|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2019-03-15|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}<br />{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/theatre-dance/reviews/betrayal-harold-pinter-theatre-review-tom-hiddleston-zawe-ashton-charlie-cox-london-a8822471.html|title=Tom Hiddleston excels in Pinter\u2019s Betrayal|date=2019-03-14|website=The Independent|language=en|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref> David Fear of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' opined that there are two sides to Hiddleston, the old-school movie star of ''[[Midnight in Paris]]'', ''[[War Horse (film)|War Horse]]'' or ''[[The Night Manager (TV series)|The Night Manager]]'', and the \"unpredictable, borderline weirdo version\" of him seen in characters like [[Loki (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Loki]] or in ''[[High-Rise (film)|High-Rise]]'', adding that Hiddleston refuses to settle on one specific kind of role.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/tv-news/how-tom-hiddleston-makes-psycho-sexy-42696/|title=How Tom Hiddleston Makes Psycho Sexy|last=Fear|first=David|date=2016-04-19|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-15}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n[[File:Tom Hiddleston, Loki (4-c).jpg|thumb|Hiddleston dressed as his character [[Loki (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Loki]] at the [[San Diego Comic-Con]] in July 2013]]\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Refs.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2006\n| ''[[Unrelated]]''\n| Oakley\n|\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2010\n| ''[[Archipelago (film)|Archipelago]]''\n| Edward\n| \n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2011\n| ''[[Midnight in Paris]]''\n| [[F. Scott Fitzgerald]]\n|\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2011\n| ''[[War Horse (film)|War Horse]]''\n| Captain Nicholls\n|\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2011\n| ''[[Friend Request Pending]]''\n| Tom\n|\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2011\n| ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]''\n| [[Loki (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Loki]]\n|\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2012\n| ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]''\n| Loki\n|\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2012\n| ''[[The Deep Blue Sea (2011 film)|The Deep Blue Sea]]''\n| Freddie Page\n|\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2012\n| ''Out of Time''\n| Man\n| Short film\n| <ref>{{cite web|last=Rothman |first=Lily |title=''Time'' Style and Design: Futuristic London Fashion |url=http://lightbox.time.com/2012/03/15/time-style-and-design-futuristic-london-fashion/#1 |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |accessdate=27 September 2012 |date=15 March 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120926050059/http://lightbox.time.com/2012/03/15/time-style-and-design-futuristic-london-fashion/ |archivedate=26 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Time Magazine {{!}} Out of Time |url=http://joshappignanesi.com/TIME-MAGAZINE-Out-Of-Time |publisher=Josh Appignanesi Official Website |accessdate